						</accessrestrict>
						<bioghist>
							<p>The World Psychiatric Association was founded in 1961 to form an association of National Societies of Psychiatry. According to the World Psychiatric Association, “The WPA is an association of national psychiatric societies aimed to increase knowledge and skills necessary for work in the field of mental health and the care for the mentally ill.” The purpose of the Association is to coordinate on a worldwide scale the activities of the member psychiatric societies and to advance inquiry into the etiology, pathology, and treatment of mental illness.</p>
						</bioghist>
